%I A394399 #17 Apr 29 2026 19:56:06
%S A394399 18,72,1152,4050,15138,20808,46818,176418,206082,281250,362952,388962,
%T A394399 472392,538722,734472,1080450,1152162,1566450,1685448,1808802,2268450,
%U A394399 2544768,4339458,4464072,4536072,6118002,6329682,7746048,9305298,14612418,14709888,16623378,18471042,19244808
%N A394399 Numbers k in A014574 (averages of twin prime pairs) such that gcd(k, sigma(k)) = 3.
%C A394399 Conjecture: all terms are of the form 2*m^2 (twice a perfect square; A001105).
%e A394399 For k = 18: sigma(18) = 39 and gcd(18, 39) = 3, so 18 is a term; moreover 18 = 2*3^2.
%e A394399 For k = 5652: sigma(5652) = 14378 and gcd(5652, 14378) = 2, so 5652 is not a term.
%o A394399 (Python)
%o A394399 from sympy import divisor_sigma, gcd, isprime
%o A394399 def ok(k):
%o A394399     return isprime(k-1) and isprime(k+1) and gcd(k, divisor_sigma(k)) == 3
%o A394399 print([k for k in range(1, 20000000) if ok(k)])
%Y A394399 Conjectural intersection of A014574, A392199 and A001105.
%Y A394399 Subsequence of A394757.
%K A394399 nonn,new
%O A394399 1,1
%A A394399 _Aied Sulaiman_, Apr 24 2026
